The individual he was exchanging with was Vincent Cerf as per the ICANN Documentation who was posting under the name Richard. He arranged a thread between the then Financial Officer of ICANN and arranged for payment for the aggreement of 50c per IPv4 Address in 2008 when he turned 30.

This aggreement is now 3 years late and has become what now ICANN look like they do not honour nor have any form of computing ethics.
